School Governing Bodies in Chatsworth in Kwazulu-Natal are calling for the closure of twelve schools in the area. This follows reports of confirmed Covid-19 cases in two schools in less than a week. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - School Governing Bodies in Chatsworth in KwaZulu-Natal are calling for the closure of 12 schools in the area. This follows reports of COVID-19 infections in two schools in less than a week. READ: Lockdown Level 3: Schools open after delay "We are saying, we can't allow for kids to become another statistic," said SGB spokesperson Brandon Pillay. "You can't allow for an increase because we know we are about to reach a peak and as a precautionary measure, other schools within the zone should close." READ: Union calls for KZN DoH to withdraw health workers loan plan Pillay says children's safety is a priority and has encouraged parents to consider keeping their children at home. Thousands of Grade 7 and 12 pupils returned to school this week after more than two months away from their desks. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.